    "_postman_id": "080cba83-29cb-47f8-97b3-db03a4c54228",
    "name": "API Test",
    "description": "EXERCISE: API TESTING\n\nObjective: Using Postman, create a suite of automated tests for the following APIs.\n\nAPI URLs:\n\nUser API: [https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users)\n\n1. Validate that the API returns a 200 status.\n    \n2. Validate that the API returns the username, address, and city fields in the response.\n    \n3. Validate that the API responds in less than 800 milliseconds.\n    \n\n---\n\nAPI comments: [https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/comments](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/comments)\n\n1. Validate that the API returns a status of 200.\n    \n2. Validate that the API returns the fields name, email, and body in the response.\n    \n3. Validate that the API responds in less than 900 milliseconds.\n    \n\n---\n\nPhoto API: [https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/photos](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/photos)\n\n1. Validate that the API returns a status of 200.\n    \n2. Validate that the API returns the fields albumId, title, and url in the response.\n    \n3. Validate that the API responds in less than 800 milliseconds.\n    \n\n---\n\nFor this specific case, you could verify that the words “username, address, and city fields” appear in the API using:\n\npm.test(“The response includes the name of the car”, function () { pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.include(“name”) });EndFragment\n\nTo perform a “more robust test,” I will convert the HTML structure into a JSON object and thus verify the correct status of the elements.\n\nThis will be repeated for the following API tests.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52846146"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"API returns username\", () => {\r",
              "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
              "\r",
              "    jsonData.forEach(user => {\r",
              "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property(\"username\");\r",
              "        pm.expect(user.username).to.be.a(\"string\");\r",
              "        \r",
              "    });\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"Each user contains address object with valid city\", () => {\r",
              "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
              "    jsonData.forEach(user => {\r",
              "        pm.expect(user).to.have.property(\"address\")\r",
              "        pm.expect(user.address).to.have.property(\"city\"); \r",
              "        pm.expect(user.address.city).to.be.a(\"string\")\r",
              "        \r",
              "    });\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"Response time is less than 800ms\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(800);\r",
              "});\r",
              "  "
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users",
          "protocol": "https",
          "host": [
            "jsonplaceholder",
            "typicode",
            "com"
          ],
          "path": [
            "users"
          ]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "comments",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"Each comment contains required fields with valid types\", () => {\r",
              "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
              "\r",
              "    jsonData.forEach(comment => {\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment).to.have.property(\"name\");\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment.name).to.be.a(\"string\");\r",
              "\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment).to.have.property(\"email\");\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment.email).to.be.a(\"string\");\r",
              "\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment).to.have.property(\"body\");\r",
              "        pm.expect(comment.body).to.be.a(\"string\");\r",
              "    });\r",
              "});\r",
              "\r",
              "pm.test(\"Response time is less than 900ms\", function () {\r",
              "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(900);\r",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
